text: The Société Générale is a French banking group, one of the three big in France.Nationalization and Privatization in Contemporary France It was founded in 1864, Paris. Now, it's head office is in La Défense, in the France, in the building known as Tours Chassagne et Alicante. Although it is a French Bank, it owns lots of banks in other countries around the world.Banque Société Générale - Faits et chiffres ==References== == Other websites == * Category:1860s establishments in France Category:1864 establishments in Europe Category:Banks of France
